by stealing tons of FTX customer money.=E2=80=9D But=C2=A0the US Internal R=
evenue Service seems to have a very different take? At CoinDesk,  Tracy Wan=
g reports:

The United States Internal Revenue Service (IRS) has filed claims worth nea=
rly $44 billion against the estate of bankrupt crypto exchange FTX and its =
affiliated entities. =E2=80=A6
The largest of the claims includes a $20.4 billion and a $7.9 billion claim=
 against Alameda Research LLC and two claims totaling $9.5 billion against =
Alameda Research Holdings Inc. ...
Bankruptcy documents detailing the $20.4 billion claim against Alameda Rese=
arch LLC reveal the IRS is claiming about $20 billion in partnership taxes.=
