I guess that  on Sam Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s estimates Alameda peaked at ab=
out $100 billion of net asset value, so $20 billion would be a reasonable t=
ax bill if that was all realized profits. On the other hand its current val=
ue is negative many billions of dollars; surely there is some offset.=C2=A0

