<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the startup boom of recent years, Tiger Glo=
bal Management got a reputation for investing in every startup, moving fast=
,=C2=A0paying top dollar and not being too involved in governance. This alw=
ays <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31488443.25843=
7/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDYtMDcvc=
mV0YWlsLXRyYWRpbmctaXMtYWJvdXQtdG8tY2hhbmdlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA1MTUyM19NT05FWVNU=
VUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDU=
xNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2e09efd3" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;"> struck me</a> as sort of a clever differentiation. A <a href=3D"https:=
//link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31488443.258437/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmx=
vb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMTMvdmNzLW5lZWQtdGhlLWdvb2=
QtdHdlZXRzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA1MTUyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX=
3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDUxNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVm=
Zg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB86029243" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> reasonable model</a> of vent=
ure capital investing,=C2=A0<em>particularly during a boom</em>, is somethi=
ng like:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Most of the returns of venture invest=
ing come from a few big home-run deals, so the trick is to be in those.</li=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Due diligence and careful deal select=
ion don=E2=80=99t matter very much: Being in the handful of big home runs a=
nd losing 100% on a bunch of other deals is better than missing some home r=
uns and avoiding most of the losers.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px=
;">Valuation doesn=E2=80=99t matter very much: Overpaying for the handful o=
f big home runs is better than missing them.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bot=
tom: 5px;">What matters is=C2=A0<em>getting into all of the good deals</em>=
, which means acquiring a reputation, with startup founders, for being easy=
 to work with.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9CEasy to wo=
rk with=E2=80=9D certainly means moving fast and paying top dollar.</li>=09=
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Some VCs clearly think that it also means=
 something like =E2=80=9Cbringing my expertise and wisdom to the board of d=
irectors,=E2=80=9D but Tiger Global=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/31488443.258437/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9v=
cGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDQtMTUvY29pbmJhc2UtZGlyZWN0LWxpc3RpbmctbmVlZGV=
kLXRoZS1jb2luLXRpY2tlcj9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNTE1MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPW=
VtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA1MTUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduP=
W1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1b44bb90" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">plausibly conclud=
ed</a> that saying =E2=80=9Cnah, we don=E2=80=99t need a board seat, we tru=
st you=E2=80=9D and=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>calling startup founders to shar=
e their wisdom would actually be received pretty well.</li>=09<li style=3D"=
margin-bottom: 5px;">Also, by moving fast, paying top dollar and not doing =
much diligence, Tiger Global got a lot of=C2=A0<em>press=C2=A0</em>=E2=80=
=94=C2=A0often quoting other VCs complaining about them =E2=80=94=C2=A0whic=
h probably inspired some startup founders to say =E2=80=9Chey, actually the=
se guys sound good, let=E2=80=99s call them.=E2=80=9D</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Just a smart approach to a certain moment in t=
he venture capital marketplace. On the other hand that moment is over and <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31488443.258437/aHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvMmY1MWU1NjgtMDI0ZC00NDMxLWFlZjEtMDYzNDc3OD=
A3ZTUx/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBada27d2d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">now here=E2=80=99s this<=
/a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Technology-focused hedge fund Tiger Global is =
exploring options to cash in a piece of its more than $40bn portfolio of pr=
ivately held companies, according to people familiar with the matter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The New York-based investment group is working=
 with an adviser to tap the so-called secondary market to help return money=
 to some of its investors, the people said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Talks are at an early stage and potential buye=
rs have said that any deal would probably be complicated by difficulties va=
luing Tiger=E2=80=99s private holdings, which include stakes in companies s=
uch as payments business Stripe, US software group Databricks and China=E2=
=80=99s ByteDance, some of the people said. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Over the past few years, investors in fast-gro=
wing companies such as Tiger have been able to realise gains by taking comp=
anies public. However, initial public offerings have slowed over the past 1=
8 months as investors grapple with wider inflationary pressures and stock m=
arket volatility. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2022, Tiger=E2=80=99s flagship fund suffere=
d its worst annual loss, losing more than 50 per cent of its value as Tiger=
 marked down its unlisted holdings by nearly 20 per cent. Some of its funds=
 have recorded small gains for unlisted assets this year, however.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And here the reputation probably does not help=
? If you go to the secondary market with a bunch of startup stakes and a re=
putation for paying top dollar and not doing much due diligence, people are=
 going to want a discount.</p>
